summary:
The Security Council,

Noting the letter from the Prime Minister of Iraq to the President of the Security Council, dated 8 December 2010,

Recognizing positive developments in Iraq and the strengthened Iraqi institutions,

Welcomes the letter from the Prime Minister of Iraq reaffirming the commitment to ensure oil revenue is used fairly and in the interests of the Iraqi people,

Recognizing the significant role of the Development Fund for Iraq and the International Advisory and Monitoring Board,

Acting under Chapter VII of the Charter of the United Nations,

1. Decides to terminate, on 30 June 2011, the arrangements established in paragraph 20 of resolution 1483 (2003) for depositing into the Development Fund for Iraq proceeds from export sales of petroleum, and related monitoring arrangements;

2. Welcomes and affirms the Government of Iraq’s decision not to request further extensions of the Development Fund for Iraq arrangements;

3. Decides that after 30 June 2011, the requirement to deposit proceeds from export sales of petroleum into the Development Fund for Iraq shall no longer apply, but 5 percent of proceeds shall continue to be deposited into the compensation fund;

4. Calls upon the Government of Iraq to work closely with the Secretary-General to finalize the transition to a post-Development Fund mechanism by 30 June 2011, and provide a written report to the Council by 1 May 2011;

5. Directs the transfer of the full proceeds from the Development Fund for Iraq to the Government of Iraq’s successor arrangements account and the termination of the Development Fund for Iraq by 30 June 2011;

6. Requests the Secretary-General to provide written reports every six months on the United Nations compensation fund, evaluating compliance with paragraph 21 of resolution 1483 (2003);
